<taxonomicName authority="Winstanley &amp; Davies, 1982: 340" authorityName="* Trib. Riviere des Pirogues, Winstanley &amp; Davies" authorityPageNumber="340" authorityYear="1982" box="[151,729,257,282]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Caledopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis box="[151,388,258,282]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Caledopteryx maculata</emphasis>
<treatmentCitation author="Winstanley, W. &amp; Davies, D." box="[394,729,257,282]" page="340" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" year="1982">
<bibRefCitation author="Winstanley, W. &amp; Davies, D." box="[394,729,257,282]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="339 - 346" refId="ref36899" refString="Winstanley, W. &amp; Davies, D. (1982) Caledopterix maculata spec. nov. from New-Caledonia (Zygoptera: Megapodagrionidae). Odonatologica, 11, 339 - 346." type="journal article" year="1982">Winstanley &amp; Davies, 1982: 340</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1184,1211]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[312,380,1184,1211]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1113,1138]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,174,1102]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,174,1102]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 6. Records of Caledopteryx maculata." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3342255/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Endemic to Grande Terre. This species reaches 
<quantity box="[927,1005,1184,1211]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" unit="mm" value="80.0">80 mm</quantity>
in wing span. It is recorded from more than 20 known localities, most of them on ultramafic soils in the south of the island. It is however recorded regularly from central 
<collectingCountry box="[354,528,1256,1283]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
sympatrically (
<bibRefCitation author="Winstanley, W. &amp; Davies, D." box="[703,1006,1256,1283]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="339 - 346" refId="ref36899" refString="Winstanley, W. &amp; Davies, D. (1982) Caledopterix maculata spec. nov. from New-Caledonia (Zygoptera: Megapodagrionidae). Odonatologica, 11, 339 - 346." type="journal article" year="1982">Winstanley &amp; Davies 1982</bibRefCitation>
) with the more northern 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ris" baseAuthorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Caledopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sarasini">Caledopteryx sarasini</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
a very similar species. For years 
<taxonomicName authorityName="* Trib. Riviere des Pirogues, Winstanley &amp; Davies" authorityYear="1982" box="[623,760,1292,1319]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Caledopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis box="[623,760,1292,1319]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">C. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was confused with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ris" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[982,1105,1293,1319]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Caledopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sarasini">
<emphasis box="[982,1105,1293,1319]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">C. sarasini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
